JavaFX UI	The GUI shows community pool usage, grid portion in percent. It has a button to refresh the usages. It enables the selection of a date range and includes a button to show the community produced, used and grid used data in kWh for the selected date range.	10%
REST API	The Spring Boot App reads the data from the database instead of using static sample data.	10%
Energy Producer	Sends production message in random 1-5 second intervals to the message queue. Production message must include a random but sensible kWh value. Weather data must be used to determine the kWh value.	10%
Energy User	Sends usage message in random 1-5 second intervals to the message queue. Usage message must include a random but sensible kWh value. Time of day must be used to determine the kWh value.	10%
Usage Service	Receives the production/usage messages and updates the usage table correctly. Afterwards sends an update message to the queue.	30%
Current Percentage Service	Receives the update message and updates the current percentage table correctly.	30%
Points can be omitted for badly written code, unsufficient presentation or the failure to explain the system.